<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">841D.24/16: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-17T19:00:00+01:00">June
                                        17, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 17—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1692. Your 1159, June 12, 1 p.m., was taken up immediately with
                                Foreign Office which has informed me today that a full reply in the
                                matter has been telegraphed to Lord Lothian<note n="3" xml:id="d152fn3">British Ambassador in the United States.</note>
                                with instructions to communicate it to the Department. The gist of
                                this reply to your inquiry is that the British Government desires
                                Lord Lothian and Mr. Purvis<note n="4" xml:id="d152fn4">Arthur B.
                                    Purvis, Director General of the British Purchasing Commission in
                                    the United States.</note> to assist the Irish Government as far
                                as possible in obtaining the material desired provided it does not
                                impede or postpone delivery of any similar material ordered by the
                                British Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>